  "text": "Findings for the 'Cannot expand this type; LLVM lacks the right hooks' assertion in llvm-project--a8f3c97d:\n\n1. SOURCE FILE WITH EXPANSION LOGIC: llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeDAG.cpp. This file contains the type legalization expansion logic. The closest match to the error message is in the SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandNode function (line 3218), which handles node expansion during SelectionDAG legalization. When expansion is impossible, related errors fire here (e.g., 'Cannot expand DIVFIX!' at line 4223). The ExpandNode function is the primary dispatch point for type expansion in the DAG legalizer.\n\n2. FUNCTION WHERE ASSERTION FIRES: SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandNode in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeDAG.cpp. Additionally, DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandFloatResult in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeFloatTypes.cpp contains 'Do not know how to expand the result of this operator!' which is triggered for unsupported float type expansions. Similarly, DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntegerResult in LegalizeIntegerTypes.cpp handles integer expansion failures.\n\n3. EVT CLASS AND isSimple() METHOD: llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/ValueTypes.h defines the EVT (Extended Value Type) struct. The isSimple() method is defined at line 137 of that file and returns true if the EVT represents a simple (non-extended) value type (i.e., an MVT).\n\n4. LegalizeDAG CLASS: The class orchestrating type legalization is SelectionDAGLegalize, defined in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeDAG.cpp (line 88). This class has a LegalizeOp method that calls ExpandNode for nodes needing expansion. The DAGTypeLegalizer class in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeTypes.h (line 31) is the complementary class that handles type-level legalization (promote/expand/split/widen) and dispatches to ExpandFloatResult, ExpandIntegerResult, etc."
}

